The paper deals with image processing tasks such as image denoising, image matting, semantic segmentation, and monocular depth estimation. It introduces a new learnable module, Index Network (IndexNet), which can be used as a plug-in applying to almost all off-the-shelf convolutional networks that have coupled downsampling and upsampling stages. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper introduces the concept of "learning to index" and presents a novel index-guided encoder-decoder framework, which involves self-learning indices from data. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also proposes a new learnable module, which suggests that it may belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with image processing tasks, which suggests that it may also belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
